es%20in%20India%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20South%20Asia%20directly%20impact%20access%20to%20water%2C%20how%20it%20is%20allocated%2C%20distributed%20and%20consumed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClimate%20change%2C%20along%20with%20oppressive%20and%20discriminatory%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fbooks%2Fclimate-justice-in-india%2Freimagining-climate-justice-as-caste-justice%2F8739A002ACA8B171A10A619A25D76BAC%5C%22%3Esocial%20practices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20makes%20a%20bad%20situation%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarginalised%20groups%20are%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1177%2F0973703020150108%5C%22%3E%20disproportionately%20affected%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20lack%20of%20attention%20to%20the%20social%20dimensions%20of%20water%20policy%2C%20its%20use%20and%20allocation%20that%20often%20perpetuate%20practices%20of%20untouchability%20and%20gender-based%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWho%20owns%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fservices%2Faop-cambridge-core%2Fcontent%2Fview%2F944A18883970B826970525435AA4A837%2Fstamped-9781009171915c9_p183-206_CBO.pdf%2Fintersectional_water_justice_in_india_at_the_confluence_of_gender_caste_and_climate_change.pdf%5C%22%3Eland%20and%20resources%20%3C%2Fa%3Ebecomes%20critical%20to%20who%20can%20access%20water.%20This%20question%20is%20determined%20along%20lines%20of%20caste%2C%20class%20and%20gender%20inequalities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommunity%20movements%20working%20towards%20equitable%20access%20to%20water%20have%20been%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2Fpdf%2F4417829.pdf%3Frefreqid%3Dfastly-default%253Ab2639e6378095eb81e40f2665a95ef7f%26ab_segments%3D0%252Fbasic_phrase_search%252Fcontrol%26origin%3D%26initiator%3Dsearch-results%26acceptTC%3D1%5C%22%3E%20stymied%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20lack%20of%20support%20by%20gram%20panchayats%20(village-level%20governance%20institutions)%20or%20by%20private%20investments%20which%20benefit%20wealthier%20farming%20communities%20with%20bigger%20landholdings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Gujarat%2C%20a%20semi-arid%20region%20in%20western%20India%20that%20relies%20on%20groundwater%20use%2C%20faces%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fservices%2Faop-cambridge-core%2Fcontent%2Fview%2F944A18883970B826970525435AA4A837%2Fstamped-9781009171915c9_p183-206_CBO.pdf%2Fintersectional_water_justice_in_india_at_the_confluence_of_gender_caste_and_climate_change.pdf%5C%22%3Ewater%20scarcity%20%3C%2Fa%3Edue%20to%20the%20proliferation%20of%20tubewells.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGroundwater%20access%20becomes%20the%20preserve%20of%20the%20upper%20castes%20through%20the%20building%20of%20tubewells%20on%20private%20land%2C%20a%20form%20of%20access%20based%20on%20casteist%20social%20structures%20that%20limit%20land%20ownership%20among%20the%20lower%20castes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20socio-economic%20status%20determines%20access%20to%20water%20and%20who%20uses%20more%20of%20the%20groundwater%20commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETubewells%20have%20resulted%20in%20the%20drying%20out%20of%20shallow%20wells%2C%20giving%20rise%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F10455752.2015.1066835%3FjournalCode%3Drcns20%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThis%2520was%2520done%2520to%2520generate%2Cknowledge%2520about%2520the%2520watershed%2520project.%26text%3DCaste%2520is%2520a%2520pan-Indian%2520phenomenon.%5C%22%3Ewater%20lords%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20who%20dominate%20consumption%20of%20water.%20This%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20forces%20poor%20farmers%20to%20rely%20further%20on%20them%20for%20water%20supply%20in%20an%20already%20exploitative%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlongside%20caste%2C%20gender%20also%20becomes%20a%20determinant%20of%20communities%E2%80%99%20relationships%20with%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWomen%20are%20the%20face%20of%20water%20poverty%20in%20India.%20The%20responsibility%20of%20meeting%20families%E2%80%99%20water%20needs%20in%20rural%20India%20falls%20