ortionately%20affect%20lower-caste%20women%2C%20subjecting%20them%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fgujarat-dalits-untouchability%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520Becharaji%2520village%2520of%2520Rantej%2Cwell%252C%2520is%2520meant%2520for%2520Dalits.%5C%22%3E%20extreme%20precarity%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20vulnerability%20to%20sexual%20abuse%20by%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20becomes%20more%20alarming%20because%20groundwater%20levels%20in%20South%20Asia%20are%20heavily%20impacted%20by%20salinity%20in%20coastal%20areas.%20Gujarat%20has%20the%20longest%20coastline%20in%20India%20and%20water%20from%20wells%20is%20already%20undrinkable%20like%20some%20villages%20in%20Jafrabad%20district%20where%20women%20are%20forced%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahmedabadmirror.com%2Fat-this-amreli-village-water-pips-jingoism-as-poll-issue%2F68928865.html%5C%22%3Ewalk%20miles%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20access%20safe%20drinking%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClimate%20change%20inflicts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahmedabadmirror.com%2Fat-this-amreli-village-water-pips-jingoism-as-poll-issue%2F68928865.html%5C%22%3Edisproportionate%20burdens%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20marginalised%20groups.%20Discriminatory%20practices%20in%20access%20to%20water%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fservices%2Faop-cambridge-core%2Fcontent%2Fview%2F944A18883970B826970525435AA4A837%2Fstamped-9781009171915c9_p183-206_CBO.pdf%2Fintersectional_water_justice_in_india_at_the_confluence_of_gender_caste_and_climate_change.pdf%5C%22%3E%20continue%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20concerns%20of%20caste%20pollution%20%E2%80%93%20a%20belief%20among%20the%20upper%20castes%20that%20their%20%E2%80%98purity%E2%80%99%20will%20be%20defiled%20if%20they%20come%20into%20contact%20with%20lower-caste%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEfforts%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fservices%2Faop-cambridge-core%2Fcontent%2Fview%2F944A18883970B826970525435AA4A837%2Fstamped-9781009171915c9_p183-206_CBO.pdf%2Fintersectional_water_justice_in_india_at_the_confluence_of_gender_caste_and_climate_change.pdf%5C%22%3E%20decentralise%3C%2Fa%3E%20water%20governance%20in%20Gujarat%20continue%20to%20meet%20resistance%20from%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20people%20for%20whom%20equity%20of%20access%20disrupts%20their%20monopoly%20over%20irrigation%20and%20agricultural%20uses.%20Maintaining%20control%20of%20water%20access%20gives%20upper%20castes%20an%20advantage%20over%20lower-caste%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20injustices%20remain%20marginal%20considerations%20for%20intervention%20by%20NGOs%20and%20state%20governments.%20The%20problem%20of%20access%20to%20public%20resources%20based%20on%20social%20difference%20thus%20needs%20to%20be%20addressed%20urgently%20by%20policy-makers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGovernments%20have%20failed%20to%20acknowledge%20social%20discrimination%20in%20the%20provision%20of%20basic%20amenities%20to%20marginalised%20communities%20which%20will%20grow%20increasingly%20vulnerable%20as%20climate%20change%20intensifies%20long-standing%20social%20disparities%20in%20wealth%20and%20resource%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImproving%20public%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fengage%2Farticle%2Fwho-will-guard-guardians-state-accountability%5C%22%3Eaccountability%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20governance%20requires%20an%20understanding%20of%20the%20effects%20of%20the%20numerous%20disadvantages%20faced%20by%20marginalised%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20India%E2%80%99s%20summer%20approaching%20and%20water%20stress%20becoming%20a%20reality%2C%20poor%20and%20marginalised%20women%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewhumanitarian.org%2Fnews-feature%2F2023%2F07%2F20%2Fits-all-our-burden-poorest-women-hardest-hit-heatwaves-india%5C%22%3Ebear%20the%20brunt%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20heat%20stress%20in%20the%20collection%20of%20water%2C%20a%20fact%20unrecognised%20by%20policymakers%20and%20insufficiently%20addressed%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Fclimate%2Findia-heat-action-plans-overlook-the-vulnerable%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520country%26amp%3Bapos%3Bs%2520first%2520Heat%2520Action%2Cas%2520moves%2520targeted%2520at%2520poor%5C%22%3EHeat%20Action%20Plans%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWater%20scarcity%20and%20water%20insecurity%20are%20created%20through%20socio-economic%20and%20political%20inequalities.%20Socially%20just%20climate%20adaptation%20for%20water%20management%20can%20go%20hand-in-hand%20with%20an%20acknowledgement%20of%20the%20social%20power%20vested%20in%20local%20elites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGenerating%20institutional%20change%20from%20both%20above%20and%20below%20requires%20addressing%20the%20various%20barriers%20that%20prevent%20achieving%20human%20rights%20for%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20communities.%20It%20also%20demands%20political%20mobilisation%20towards%20overcoming%20social%20barriers%20in%20the%20same%20vein%20as%20the%20Mahad%20Satyagraha%20of%201927.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiving%20everyone%20a%20say%20in%20decision-making%20and%20removing%20unequal%20administrative%20measures%20that%20prevent%20fair%20access%20to%20water%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20making%20tubewells%20a%20public%20good%20with%20parameters%20of%20equal%20access%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20pursued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegal%20provisions%20towards%20supporting%20water%20equality%20need%20to%20be%20made%20enforceable.%20Otherwise%20the%20idea%20of%20water%20justice%20remains%20a%20mere%20tokenism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EPrakash%20Kashwan%20is%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholarworks.brandeis.edu%2Fesploro%2Fprofile%2Fprakash_kashwan%2Foverview%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EAssociate%20Professor%20of%20Environmental%20Studies%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20and%20Chair%2C%20Environmental%20Justice%20Concentration%2C%20MPP%2C%20at%20the%20Heller%20School%20for%20Social%20Policy%20%26amp%3B%20Management%20at%20Brandeis%20University.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%20Democracy%20in%20the%20Woods%3A%20Environmental%20Conservation%20and%20Social%20Justice%20in%20India%2C%20Tanzania%2C%20and%20Mexico%20(Oxford%20University%20Press%2C%202017)%20and%20the%20Editor%20of%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fbooks%2Fclimate-justice-in-india%2F9728CA91D37ABECD4816C16BA3198873%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EClimate%20Justice%20in%20India%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20(Cambridge%20University%20Press%2C%202022).%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20by%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E360info%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%84%A2.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711115151000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19165415%2Fimage-1409.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Faccess-to-water-is-a-crisis-for-the-powerless%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fair%20access%20to%20water%20is%20an%20issue%20for%20millions%20of%20people%20in%20India.%20Who%20controls%20access%20and%20how%20this%20is%20governed%20needs%20fixing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Faccess-to-water-is-a-crisis-for-the-powerless%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222020%20Delhi%20Riots%3A%20Those%20Facing%20Graver%20Allegations%20Granted%20Bail%2C%20Says%20Umar%20Khalid%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F18112637%2FUmar-Khalid.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20the%202020%20Northeast%20Delhi%20riots%20%E2%80%98larger%20conspiracy%20case%E2%80%99%2C%20arguing%20for%20bail%2C%20Umar%20Khalid%20said%20that%20others%20with%20graver%20allegations%20were%20out%20on%20bail%20and%20some%20allegedly%20involved%20in%20similar%20activities%20weren%E2%80%99t%20accused%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fdelhi%2Fdelhi-riots-larger-conspiracy-case-granted-bail-umar-khalid-9226972%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhalid%20faced%20charges%20under%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%20(UAPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20he%20withdrew%20his%20bail%20plea%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20His%20lawyer%2C%20Senior%20Advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20cited%20a%20%E2%80%9Cchange%20in%20circumstances%E2%80%9D%20and%20planned%20to%20pursue%20bail%20in%20the%20trial%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20try%20our%20luck%20in%20the%20trial%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%20(March%2021)%2C%20advocate%20Trideep%20Pais%2C%20appearing%20for%20Khalid%2C%20revealed%20the%20change%20of%20circumstances%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Karkardooma%20Court%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20factual%20basis%20on%20which%20three%20accused%20in%20the%20case%20have%20been%20granted%20bail%20have%20several%20overlaps%20with%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Pais.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20argued%20that%20the%20court%20could%20consider%20if%20Khalid%20was%20entitled%20to%20a%20bail%20of%20parity%20even%20though%20he%20was%20charged%20with%20the%20stringent%20UAPA%20as%20the%20law%20was%20interpreted%20differently%20by%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20in%202023%2C%20the%20daily%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20court%20must%20be%20satisfied%20with%20the%20probative%20value%20of%20evidence%20at%20the%20stage%20of%20examining%20bail%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Pais%2C%20adding%20that%20no%20terrorist%20act%20had%20been%20attributed%20to%20the%20accused%20by%20the%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20change%20of%20circumstances%20cited%20by%20the%20advocate%20was%20the%20continued%20incarceration%20of%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20cited%20Pais%20as%20saying%20that%20the%20prosecution%20cited%2015%20instances%20to%20point%20out%20the%20involvement%20of%20the%20accused%20%E2%80%93%20in%20many%20of%20these%2C%20there%20were%20no%20witnesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPais%20said%20the%20prosecution%20also%20mentioned%20four%20WhatsApp%20groups%20in%20the%20chargesheet%20to%20allege%20a%20conspiracy%20%E2%80%93%20out%20of%20these%2C%20he%20said%20Khalid%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20part%20of%20two%20groups.%20He%20alleged%20that%20many%20persons%20in%20these%20two%20groups%20were%20not%20even%20made%20an%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20one%20group%2C%20Khalid%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20send%20a%20single%20message.%20In%20the%20fourth%20WhatsApp%20group%20which%20Khalid%20was%20a%20part%20of%2C%20he%20sent%20only%20five%20messages%20%E2%80%93%20three%20of%20which%20were%20Google%20Maps%20locations%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20daily%20quoted%20Pais%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhalid%20also%20put%20up%20a%20message%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20police%20to%20call%20off%20the%20protest%2C%20claimed%20Pais.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20accused%20never%20instigated%20violence%20through%20this%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20two%20accused%20who%20were%20in%20Northeast%20Delhi%20during%20the%20riots%20are%20on%20bail.%20They%E2%80%99re%20in%20the%20same%20group%20as%20me%E2%80%A6%20they%E2%80%99re%20far%20more%20involved%20in%20the%20group%E2%80%A6%20a%20witness%20also%20made%20a%20direct%20allegation%20of%20rioting%20against%20these%20two%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Pais.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20are%20just%20two%20of%20the%20seven%20persons%20being%20made%20an%20accused%3F%20What%20makes%20them%20stand%20out%3F%E2%80%9D%20said%20Pais%2C%20adding%20that%20participation%20in%20a%20meeting%20whose%20contents%20were%20unknown%20to%20the%20prosecution%20was%20not%20illegal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPais%20cited%20an%20instance%20where%20there%20was%20a%20witness%2C%20noting%20that%20his%20statements%2C%20when%20compared%20with%20the%20chargesheet%2C%20were%20incorrect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20granted%20bail%20to%20co-accused%20Asif%20Iqbal%20Tanha%20despite%20the%20same%20witness%20attributing%20more%20severe%20crimes%20to%20Tanha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Pais%20mentioned%20another%20instance%20where%20the%20prosecution%20alleged%20that%20three%20accused%20had%20conspired%20in%20Shaheen%20Bagh%2C%20but%20argued%20that%20the%20accused%20were%20not%20visible%20in%20any%20CCTV%20footage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPais%20also%20argued%20that%20in%20other%20instances%20of%20meetings%20with%20other%20co-accused%2C%20their%20CDRs%20didn%E2%80%99t%20match%20with%20Khalid%E2%80%99s.%20%E2%80%9CThey%E2%80%99re%20all%20at%20different%20locations%E2%80%A6%20how%20did%20they%20plan%20a%20grand%20conspiracy%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20time%20India%20announced%20that%20(then%20US%20President%20Donald)%20Trump%20would%20visit%20(was)%20on%20January%2013.%20The%20prosecution%20claims%20that%20the%20accused%20gathered%20on%20January%208%20to%20disrupt%20his%20event%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20nobody%20even%20knew%20that%20Trump%20was%20coming%20to%20India%20on%20January%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20Khalid%2C%20the%20other%20individuals%20accused%20in%20the%20case%20are%20Devangana%20Kalita%2C%20Natasha%20Narwal%2C%20Asif%20Iqbal%20Tanha%2C%20former%20AAP%20councillor%20Tahir%20Hussain%2C%20Khalid%20Saifi%2C%20ex-Congress%20councillor%20Ishrat%20Jahan%2C%20Safoora%20Zargar%2C%20Sharjeel%20Imam%2C%20Meeran%20Haider%2C%20Gulfisha%20Fatima%2C%20Shifa-Ur-Rehman%2C%20Shadab%20Ahmed%2C%20Tasleem%20Ahmed%2C%20Saleem%20Malik%2C%20Mohd.%20Saleem%20Khan%2C%20Athar%20Khan%2C%20and%20Faizal%20Khan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Tanha%2C%20Narwal%2C%20and%20Kalita%20have%20been%20released%20on%20bail%2C%20the%20remaining%2014%20accused%20have%20been%20incarcerated%20for%20the%20past%20four%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpolice-witness-not-credible-callous-probe-how-the-delhi-riots-cases-have-evolved%5C%22%3Ehad%20earlier%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20judges%20rapped%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20for%20%E2%80%98biased%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98improper%E2%80%99%20investigation%20into%20the%20Delhi%20riots.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20courts%20have%20rapped%20the%20Delhi%20Police%2C%20which%20comes%20under%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FDelhi%2F2020-delhi-riots-fabricated-evidence-hostile-witness-and-a-case-of-shoddy-probe%2Farticle66955373.ece%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98fabrication%20of%20evidence%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FDelhi%2F2020-delhi-riots-fabricated-evidence-hostile-witness-and-a-case-of-shoddy-probe%2Farticle66955373.ece%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98shoddy%20probe%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-police-northeast-riots-investigation%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%98a%20lack%20of%20logic%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711114240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F18112637%2FUmar-Khalid.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2F2020-delhi-riots-those-facing-graver-allegations-granted-bail-says-umar-khalid%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20February%2C%20Khalid%20withdrew%20his%20bail%20plea%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20His%20lawyer%2C%20Senior%20Advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20cited%20a%20%26quot%3Bchange%20in%20circumstances%26quot%3B%20and%20planned%20to%20pursue%20bail%20in%20the%20trial%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2F2020-delhi-riots-those-facing-graver-allegations-granted-bail-says-umar-khalid%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22World%20Water%20Day%202024%3A%20Why%20Water%20Is%20Important%20For%20Peace%20At%20An%20Individual%2C%20Community%20and%20Global%20Level%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22182534%2FScreenshot-2024-03-22-at-6.21.38-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20theme%20for%20World%20Water%20Day%202024%2C%20observed%20on%20March%2022%2C%20is%20%E2%80%98Water%20for%20Peace%E2%80%99.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20question%20that%20one%20should%20ask%20is%2C%20how%20does%20water%20bring%20peace%3F%20Peace%20for%20whom%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0individuals%2C%20nations%2C%20continents%20or%20our%20planet%3F%20Why%20are%20we%20distressed%20about%20it%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWater%20is%20not%20only%20a%20%E2%80%98vital%20substance%E2%80%99%20for%20human%20existence%20but%20is%20also%20a%20%E2%80%98peace%20keeper%E2%80%99.%20Acknowledging%20the%20collective%20action%20on%20conserving%20water%2C%20reflecting%20on%20community-based%20practices%20of%20water%20management%20can%20help%20us%20locate%20the%20role%20of%20water%20in%20bringing%20peace%20to%20individuals%2C%20communities%20and%20humanity.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHistorically%20speaking%2C%20shortage%20of%20water%20has%20brought%20distress%2C%20migration%20and%20violence.%20Societies%20that%20manage%20their%20water%20judiciously%20have%20largely%20been%20peaceful.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPeace%20for%20individuals%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20present%2C%20the%20most%20crucial%20issue%20that%20lies%20before%20us%20is%20that%20of%20global%20climate%20change.%20Increasing%20number%20of%20people%20are%20now%20turning%20into%20%E2%80%98climate%20refugees%E2%80%99%20i.e.%20individuals%20who%20are%20forced%20to%20leave%20their%20country%20due%20to%20short-term%20or%20long-term%20climate%20crises%20like%20drought%2C%20flood%2C%20deforestation%20etc.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20These%20individuals%20live%20a%20distressed%20and%20undignified%20life%2C%20bordered%20nation-states%20inflict%20violence%20on%20them%2C%20considering%20them%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20domestic%20population.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20High%20Commissioner%20for%20Refugees%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EUNHCR)%2C%20%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unhcr.org%2Fin%2Fnews%2Fstories%2Ffrequently-asked-questions-climate-change-and-disaster-displacement%5C%22%3E21.5%20million%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20an%20average%20are%20forcibly%20displaced%20each%20year%20because%20of%20climate-related%20problems.%20An%20internationally%20acclaimed%20think%20tank%2C%20Institute%20for%20Economics%20and%20Peace%20(IEP)%2C%20predicts%20that%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economicsandpeace.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2FEcological-Threat-Register-Press-Release-27.08-FINAL.pdf%5C%22%3E%201.2%20billion%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20dislocated%20globally%20by%202050%20due%20to%20environmental%20change%2C%20conflict%20and%20civil%20unrest.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20conservation%20and%20management%20of%20limited%20water%20resources%20would%20guarantee%20peace%20in%20the%20lives%20of%20people%20and%20ensure%20that%20they%20attain%20a%20dignified%20livelihood%20in%20their%20own%20country%20or%20region.%20For%20instance%2C%20due%20to%20water%20scarcity%20in%20Dholpur%20and%20Karauli%20districts%20in%20Rajasthan%20many%20local%20residents%20led%20a%20life%20of%20desperation%20and%20even%20migrated%20to%20work%20as%20labourers%20which%20resulted%20in%20family%20fragmentation%20etc.%20Moreover%2C%20some%20people%20in%20these%20areas%20even%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eresorted%20to%20illegal%20occupation%20like%20dacoity.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20the%20efforts%20of%20NGOs%20such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ETarun%20Bharat%20Sangh%20spanning%20over%20decades%2C%20dead%20perennial%20rivers%20%E2%80%94%20Sairni%20and%20Parvati%20%E2%80%94%20were%20rejuvenated%20in%20this%20region.%20So%2C%20when%20the%20area%20started%20getting%20water%2C%20the%20gun%20toting%20men%20turned%20to%20agriculture.%20This%20is%20how%20water%20brought%20peace%20to%20individuals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPeace%20for%20community%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnly%20peaceful%20individuals%20can%20create%20and%20sustain%20peaceful%20communities.%20Water%20is%20essential%20to%20bring%20peace%20within%20and%20among%20communities.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20also%20true%20that%20community%20efforts%20are%20more%20important%20than%20individuals%20to%20effectively%20conserve%20water%20resources.%20There%20is%20a%20growing%20acknowledgement%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20community%20practices%20of%20water%20management.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecently%2C%20United%20Nations%20Educational%2C%20Scientific%20and%20Cultural%20Organisation%20(UNESCO)%20chair%20in%20community-based%20research%20and%20social%20responsibility%20in%20higher%20education%20released%20a%20book%20titled%2C%20%3Cem%3EBridging%20Knowledge%20Cultures%3A%20Rebalancing%20power%20in%20the%20co-construction%20of%20Knowledge%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0edited%20by%20Walter%20Lepore%2C%20Budd%20L.%20Hall%20and%20Rajesh%20Tandon.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20book%20talks%20about%20ten%20authentic%20case%20studies%20of%20community%20knowledge%20cultures.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fcaste-water-access-missing-india-environmental-discourse%5C%22%3ECaste%E2%80%99s%20Role%20in%20Shaping%20Water%20Access%20Is%20Missing%20From%20Indian%20Environmental%20Discourse%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETarun%20Bharat%20Sangh%20has%20itself%20published%20two%20books%20%3Cem%3ERejuvenation%20of%20rivers%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0published%20in%202022%20and%20%3Cem%3EDecentralised%20and%20equitable%20climate%20resilience%20through%20community%20knowledge%2C%20rainwater%20capture%20%3C%2Fem%3Epublished%20in%202023%20highlights%20how%20the%20local%20community%20knowledge%20of%20rainwater%20harvesting%2C%20constructing%20and%20maintaining%20traditional%20water%20bodies%20like%3Cem%3E%20johads%2C%20nadas%2C%20nadis%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20been%20instrumental%20in%20reviving%20dead%20perennial%20rivers%20like%20Agrani%2C%20Maharani%2C%20Sherni%2C%20etc.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20authors%20of%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20(IPCC)%20synthesis%20reports%20might%2C%20however%2C%20not%20consider%20the%20narratives%20of%20communities%20as%20authentic%20sources%20of%20information.%20They%20rather%20rely%20on%20academically%20sanctioned%20%E2%80%98peer-reviewed%E2%80%99%20articles.%20The%20climate%2Fenvironmental%20scientists%20who%20dominate%20the%20domain%20of%20global%20climate%20policy%20fail%20to%20understand%20the%20essence%20of%20community%20knowledge%20culture%20as%20they%20lack%20the%20framework%20to%20do%20so.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20different%20UN%20bodies%20have%20completely%20different%20outlook%20towards%20community%20knowledge.%20To%20bring%20peace%20in%20the%20community%20through%20water%2C%20we%20need%20an%20alternative%20theoretical%20and%20methodological%20framework%20to%20understand%20and%20respect%20community%20knowledge%20cultures%20of%20water%20conservation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPeace%20for%20humanity%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr.%20Rajendra%20Singh%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20the%20Waterman%20of%20India%2C%20highlighted%20that%20constructive%20and%20collective%20action%20to%20conserve%20and%20manage%20water%20will%20only%20be%20possible%20when%20we%20challenge%20the%20modern%20science%20that%20favours%20command%20and%20control%20technology%20and%20anthropocentric%20misuse%20of%20water%20commons.%20He%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%98science%20without%20sense%E2%80%99%20that%20has%20overdrafted%2062%25%20of%20underground%20aquifers%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20People%E2%80%99s%20science%20or%20people%E2%80%99s%20knowledge%20is%20epistemologically%20contradictory%20to%20modern%20science%2C%20it%20has%20an%20outlook%20of%20respect%20and%20nourishment%20towards%20commons%20unlike%20the%20one%20of%20control%20and%20exploitation%20held%20by%20the%20latter.%20Our%20imagination%20of%20development%20is%20appropriated%20by%20a%20%E2%80%98universal%20path%20of%20modern%20development%20backed%20by%20western%20science%E2%80%99%2C%20cognitive%20peace%20would%20come%20if%20we%20look%20at%20the%20pluriverse%20of%20knowledge(s)%20to%20govern%20commons%20that%20are%20already-existing%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20world%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20Global%20South.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20philosophies%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20like%20Swaraj%20(Asia)%2C%20Buen%20Vivir%20(South%20America)%2C%20Ubuntu%20(Africa)%20etc.%20offer%20alternative%20sustainable%20pathways%20to%20manage%20commons%20and%20help%20us%20gain%20cognitive%20peace%2C%20the%20most%20essential%20one%20for%20humanity.%20Any%20efforts%2C%20individual%20or%20communal%2C%20modern%20or%20traditional%2C%20global%20or%20local%20would%20likely%20fail%20until%20we%20free%20ourselves%20%E2%80%98cognitively%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98growth%20monster%E2%80%99%20within%20ourselves.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20really%20need%20%E2%80%98Swaraj%20in%20ideas%E2%80%99%20to%20think%20beyond%20the%20modern%20hydraulic%20approach%20of%20water%20management.%20We%20need%20to%20focus%20on%20alternative%20pathways%20for%20water%20management%20especially%20the%20the%20Global%20South%20for%20peaceful%20co-existence.%20The%20frameworks%20of%20community%20knowledge%20have%20to%20be%20epistemically%20imbibed%20to%20claim%20that%20water%20can%20bring%20peace%20for%20the%20entire%20humanity.%20Thus%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20internalise%20the%20theme%20of%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20World%20Water%20Day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EPuneet%20Kumar%20is%20a%20doctoral%20candidate%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Political%20Science%2C%20University%20of%20Delhi.%20He%20works%20on%20politics%20of%20knowledge%20around%20urban%20water%20bodies%20in%20Delhi.%20He%20is%20a%20member%20of%20Yuva%20Jal%20Biradari%20and%20has%20also%20volunteered%20with%20Tarun%20Bharat%20Sangh%20to%20conserve%20traditional%20water%20bodies%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20Haryana.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711112440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22182534%2FScreenshot-2024-03-22-at-6.21.38-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fworld-water-day-2024-why-water-is-important-for-peace-at-an-individual-community-and-global-level%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20philosophies%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20like%20Swaraj%20(Asia)%2C%20Buen%20Vivir%20(South%20America)%2C%20Ubuntu%20(Africa)%20etc.%20offer%20alternative%20sustainable%20pathways%20to%20manage%20commons%20and%20help%20us%20gain%20cognitive%20peace%2C%20the%20most%20essential%20one%20for%20humanity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fworld-water-day-2024-why-water-is-important-for-peace-at-an-individual-community-and-global-level%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Over%20Half%20of%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20Electoral%20Bond%20Donations%20Came%20from%20Santiago%20Martin%20and%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%E2%80%99s%20Firms%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F17133238%2FScreen-Shot-2018-05-17-at-1.32.17-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKolkata%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EChennai-based%20Future%20Gaming%20And%20Hotel%20Services%20and%20RP%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%20group%20of%20companies%20donated%20Rs%20542%20crore%20and%20Rs%20464%20crore%2C%20respectively%2C%20to%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%2C%20making%20up%2059%25%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20total%20donations%20of%20Rs%201%2C705%20crore%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20show%20latest%20data%20released%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOn%20Thursday%20evening%2C%20March%2021%2C%20the%20ECI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwho-were-the-top-buyers-of-electoral-bonds-paying%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20new%20dataset%20on%20its%20website%20containing%20alphanumeric%20numbers%20that%20help%20match%20the%20purchasers%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20with%20the%20political%20parties%20that%20received%20the%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESantiago%20Martin%E2%80%99s%20company%2C%20Future%20Gaming%20And%20Hotel%20Services%2C%20purchased%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%201%2C368%20crore%2C%20and%20emerged%20as%20the%20top%20donor%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20ECI%20data%20shows%20those%20firms%20that%20faced%20central%20agency%20probes%20have%20donated%20mostly%20to%20opposition%20parties%20and%20gave%20more%20money%20to%20West%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20party%20than%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%2C%20the%20ruling%20party%20in%20Martin%E2%80%99s%20home%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFuture%20Gaming%20And%20Hotel%20Services%20is%20the%20sole%20franchise%20owner%20of%20%E2%80%98Dear%20Lottery%E2%80%99%20in%20West%20Bengal.%20It%20is%20the%20most%20popular%20lottery%20in%20the%20state%20and%20has%20in%20the%20past%20run%20into%20multiple%20controversies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Comptroller%20and%20Audit%20General%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%202017%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcags-2017-report-flagged-serious-irregularities-by-future-gaming-top-purchaser-of-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20flagged%20serious%20irregularities%20by%20the%20company.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20launched%20a%20money%20laundering%20investigation%20against%20Martin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOver%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20at%20least%20three%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fpolitics%2Frigged-says-bjp-after-the-wife-of-tmc-mla-hits-rs-1-crore-jackpot-in-lottery%2F1187809%2F%5C%22%3ETMC%20leaders%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20won%20Rs%201%20crore%20in%20these%20lotteries.%20Opposition%20parties%20had%20called%20the%20results%20rigged%20and%20accused%20ruling%20party%20leaders%20of%20encouraging%20lottery%20addiction.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Ftmc-anubrata-mondal-his-daughter-won-lottery-cbi-2296066-2022-11-11%5C%22%3EAnubrata%20Mandal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20jailed%20Birbhum%20district%20chief%20of%20TMC%2C%20had%20his%20family%20alone%20winning%20lotteries%20thrice%2C%20prompting%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20to%20probe%20Mandal%E2%80%99s%20lottery%20luck.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20main%20electoral%20funding%20came%20from%20a%20company%20headquartered%20outside%2C%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20political%20funder%20favoured%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFour%20firms%2C%20part%20of%20the%20Kolkata-based%20M.K.%20Jalan%20group%20of%20companies%2C%20which%20include%20Keventers%2C%20have%20emerged%20as%20the%20third%20biggest%20political%20donor%20in%20the%20country%20with%20Rs%20616.9%20crore%20spending%2C%20next%20only%20to%20Future%20Gaming%20And%20Hotel%20Services%20and%20Telangana-based%20Megha%20Engineering%20(Rs%20966%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Jalans%20are%20followed%20by%20the%20Kolkata-based%20RP%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%20group%2C%20the%20fourth-highest%20spender%20in%20the%20country%2C%20having%20donated%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20609%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fchart-the-top-50-purchasers-of-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3EChart%3A%20The%20Top%2050%20Purchasers%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20by%20Promoter%2FGroup%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFunding%20pattern%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EData%20shows%20the%20two%20biggest%20political%20donors%20from%20Bengal%20%E2%80%93%20the%20M.K.%20Jalan%20group%20and%20RP%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%20group%20%E2%80%93%20took%20distinctly%20different%20funding%20trajectories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EJalan%E2%80%99s%20funding%20overwhelmingly%20favoured%20the%20BJP%2C%20with%20Rs%20351.9%20crore%20or%2057%25%20of%20its%20donation%2C%20followed%20by%20Rs%20160.5%20crore%20to%20the%20Congress%20and%20Rs%2084.4%20crore%20to%20the%20TMC.%20The%20largest%20portion%20was%20allocated%20to%20the%20BJP%20during%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EGoenka%20heavily%20favoured%20the%20TMC%2C%20giving%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20party%2076%25%20of%20its%20total%20spending%20on%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThere%20was%20another%20difference%20in%20their%20funding%20pattern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Jalans%E2%80%99%20largest%20expenditure%20incurred%20during%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20in%20April-May%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOf%20the%20Rs%20390.5%20crore%2C%20the%20company%20gave%20Rs%20325%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20Rs%2031%20crore%20to%20the%20TMC%2C%20Rs%2024%20crore%20to%20the%20Congress%2C%20Rs%2010%20crore%20to%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20and%20Rs%2050%20lakh%20to%20the%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Goenkas%20gave%20Rs%2015%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP%20and%20Rs%205%20crore%20to%20the%20TMC%20during%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20April%202021%2C%20during%20the%20state%20assembly%20elections%2C%20the%20company%20gave%20Rs%2041%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP%20and%20Rs%2036%20crore%20to%20the%20TMC.%20However%2C%20after%20Mamata%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20return%20to%20power%2C%20funds%20flew%20into%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20accounts%20in%20rather%20large%20sums.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Jalan%20group%E2%80%99s%20funding%20to%20the%20Congress%20is%20interesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENote%20that%20Congress%20leader%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20unit%20president%2C%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%2C%20had%20in%202018%20filed%20a%20case%20in%20the%20Calcutta%20high%20court%20alleging%20irregularities%20in%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20Metro%20Dairy%20to%20the%20Jalan%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fbusiness%2Fchallenge-to-metro-dairy-selloff-spiked%2Fcid%2F1887104%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20was%20alleged%20that%20there%20was%20lack%20of%20transparency%20in%20the%20Bengal%20government%E2%80%99s%20sale%20of%20its%2047%25%20stake%20in%20Metro%20Dairy%20to%20Keventer%20Agro%20Ltd%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20high%20court%20dismissed%20these%20allegations%2C%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-adhir-ranjan-chowdhury-metro-dairy-disinvestment-tmc-govt-209537%5C%22%3Eupheld%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20verdict%20the%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20donors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOutside%20of%20these%20three%20firms%2C%20the%20TMC%20also%20got%20substantial%20donations%20from%20several%20other%20companies%20%E2%80%93%20Rs%2045.5%20crore%20from%20Avees%20Trading%20Finance%20Pvt%20Ltd%2C%20Rs%2042%20crore%20from%20IFB%20Agro%2C%20Rs%2040%20crore%20from%20Chennai%20Green%20Woods%20Pvt%20Ltd%2C%20and%20Rs%2038%20crore%20Prarambh%20Securities%20Pvt%20Ltd.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOther%20major%20donations%20to%20the%20TMC%20include%20Rs%2021%20crore%20from%20Transways%20Exim%20Private%20Limited%2C%20Rs%2018.5%20crore%20from%20Rashmi%20Cement%20Ltd%2C%20Rs.%2015.4%20crore%20from%20Westwell%20Gases%20Pvt%20Ltd%2C%20Rs.%2015%20crore%20from%20Misrilall%20Mines%2C%20Rs%2015%20crore%20from%20WPIL%20and%20Rs%2012.8%20crore%20from%20Himalayan%20Endeavour%20Pvt%20Ltd.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAmong%20them%2C%20Chennai%20Green%20Woods%20Pvt%20Ltd%20is%20based%20in%20Hyderabad%20and%20Prarambh%20Securities%20Pvt%20Ltd%20has%20its%20registered%20office%20in%20Gujarat%20and%20corporate%20office%20in%20Maharashtra.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20companies%20are%20headquartered%20in%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOf%20these%20companies%2C%20Avees%20has%20also%20given%20Rs%2053%20crore%20to%20the%20Congress%2C%20IFB%20gave%20Rs%2035%20crore%20to%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%2C%20Rashmi%20Cement%20gave%20Rs%2072%20crore%20to%20Odisha%E2%80%99s%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20and%20WPIL%20gave%20Rs%2015%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOther%20donors%20of%20the%20party%20include%20Sengupta%20And%20Sengupta%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(Rs.%208.2%20crore)%2C%20Sandeep%20Auto%20Lines%20(7%20crore)%2C%20Tivoli%20Park%20Apartments%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(7%20crore)%2C%20Kamna%20Credits%20And%20Promoters%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(6%20crore)%2C%20Askus%20Logistics%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(5%20crore)%2C%20Asish%20Finance%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(5%20crore)%2C%20Herald%20Beverages%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(Rs%205.5%20crore)%2C%20ITC%20Ltd%20(Rs%204.9%20crore)%2C%20KVR%20Baseline%20Resources%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(Rs%204%20crore)%2C%20Kejriwal%20Miiniing%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(Rs%204%20crore)%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20Waste%20Management%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(Rs%206%20crore)%20and%20Salasar%20Stock%20Broking%20Ltd-Proprietary%20(Rs%205%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20party%2C%20which%20has%20been%20ruling%20Bengal%20since%202011%2C%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20third-highest%20recipient%20of%20political%20donations%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%20Its%20earning%20of%20Rs%201%2C705%20crore%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20comes%20next%20only%20to%20the%20BJP%20and%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20Rajya%20Sabha%20members%20like%20Saket%20Gokhale%20and%20Jawhar%20Sircar%20have%20repeatedly%20used%20social%20media%20to%20target%20the%20BJP%20over%20alleged%20misuse%20of%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Scheme%2C%20none%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20senior%20leaders%20in%20West%20Bengal%20have%20commented%20in%20the%20past%20five%20weeks%20since%20the%20scrapping%20of%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EReacting%20to%20the%20revelations%2C%20CPI(M)%20state%20secretary%20Md.%20Salim%20said%20last%20week%20that%20the%20data%20made%20it%20evident%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccorporates%20conspired%20against%20the%20Leftists%20to%20ensure%20there%20are%20no%20Left%20MPs%20from%20Bengal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHe%20alleged%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccorporates%20funded%20the%20two%20pro-corporate%20parties%E2%80%9D%20to%20create%20a%20political%20binary%20around%20the%20TMC%20and%20the%20BJP%20%E2%80%9Cso%20that%20they%20can%20loot%20and%20share%20the%20spoils%20in%20perfect%20understanding.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20CPI(M)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthree-left-parties-declared-to-ec-that-they-dont-accept-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3Edid%20not%20accept%20any%20donation%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20was%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Scheme.%20The%20party%20has%20no%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20in%20the%20state%20since%202019%20and%20no%20MLA%20since%202021%2C%20as%20its%20vote%20share%20nosedived.%20Currently%2C%20the%20party%20is%20trying%20to%20highlight%20the%20massive%20corporate%20funding%20from%20Bengal%20corporates%20to%20these%20two%20parties%20to%20regain%20lost%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThey%20are%20set%20to%20contest%20the%20election%20in%20alliance%20with%20the%20Congress%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20even%20as%20the%20party%20will%20fight%20the%20Congress%20in%20Kerala%2C%20which%20the%20CPI(M)%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711108060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F17133238%2FScreen-Shot-2018-05-17-at-1.32.17-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fover-half-of-tmcs-electoral-bond-donations-came-from-santiago-martin-and-sanjiv-goenkas-firms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chennai-based%20Future%20Gaming%20And%20Hotel%20Services%2C%20owned%20by%20Martin%2C%20was%2C%20however%2C%20the%20biggest%20political%20donor%20to%20the%20BJP.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fover-half-of-tmcs-electoral-bond-donations-came-from-santiago-martin-and-sanjiv-goenkas-firms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Students%2C%20Historians%20Enraged%20As%20Administration%20Cuts%20Poplar%20Trees%20In%20Kashmir's%20Second%20Oldest%20College%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22160203%2FScreenshot-2024-03-22-at-3.59.55.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20An%20UNESCO-awarded%20colonial-era%20building%20in%20Srinagar%2C%20the%20summer%20capital%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20been%20allegedly%20vandalised.%20The%20development%20has%20angered%20students%2C%20heritage%20conservationists%2C%20historians%20and%20environmentalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20local%20administration%20has%20justified%20the%20culling%20of%20dozens%20of%20poplar%20trees%20along%20a%20scenic%20avenue%20in%20Amar%20Singh%20College%2C%20which%20is%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20second%20oldest%20college.%20According%20to%20official%20documents%2C%20a%20tender%20was%20floated%20by%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20State%20Forest%20Corporation%20on%20May%2029%2C%202019%2C%20for%20removing%20the%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProf%20Sheikh%20Aijaz%20Bashir%2C%20the%20college%20principal%2C%20said%20that%20the%20proposal%20was%20mooted%20in%202019%20when%20he%20was%20not%20at%20the%20helm%20and%20the%20process%20culminated%20earlier%20this%20month%20with%20the%20removal%20of%20234%20poplar%20and%20willow%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20trees%20were%20decaying%20and%20posed%20a%20threat%20to%20life%20and%20property%2C%E2%80%9D%20Prof%20Bashir%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CTo%20ensure%20the%20safety%20of%20more%20than%204000%20college%20students%20and%20staff%2C%20they%20had%20to%20be%20removed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20forest%20department%20official%20confirmed%20that%20the%20college%20had%20referred%20the%20trees%20for%20evaluation%20to%20the%20Social%20Forestry%20Department%20after%20which%20they%20were%20put%20up%20for%20auction.%20However%2C%20the%20official%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20provide%20the%20evaluation%20report%20of%20the%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20listed%20heritage%20college%20and%20a%20Grade-1%20heritage%20structure%2C%E2%80%9D%20Srinagar-based%20art%20conservator%20and%20historian%20Saleem%20Beg%20mentioned%2C%20adding%20that%20that%20the%20plantation%2C%20which%20was%20an%20attraction%20among%20filmmakers%20and%20tourists%20in%20the%20city%2C%20has%20been%20a%20part%20of%20the%20original%20layout%20that%20synchronised%20the%20entries%2C%20pathways%20and%20buildings%20of%20the%20college%20which%20was%20built%20in%201913.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22160932%2FScreenshot-2024-03-22-at-3.59.45.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22160932%2FScreenshot-2024-03-22-at-3.59.45.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22160932%2FScreenshot-2024-03-22-at-3.59.45-300x202.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22160932%2FScreenshot-2024-03-22-at-3.59.45-1024x689.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-702848%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22808%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDozens%20of%20poplar%20trees%20were%20removed%20from%20a%20scenic%20avenue%20in%20Amar%20Singh%20College%2C%20which%20is%20a%20listed%20heritage%20college%20and%20a%20Grade-1%20heritage%20structure.%20Photo%3A%20Ubaid%20Mukhtar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20very%20inappropriate%20decision.%20The%20avenue%20has%20been%20the%20essential%20part%20of%20the%20built%20fabric%20that%20linked%20the%20main%20building%20with%20its%20natural%20settings.%20The%20college%20management%20should%20have%20retained%20the%20natural%20setting%20by%20protecting%20these%20trees.%20They%20should%20have%20known%20better%2C%E2%80%9D%20Beg%2C%20who%20is%20the%20convener%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Chapter%20of%20Indian%20National%20Trust%20for%20Art%20and%20Cultural%20Heritage%20(INTACH)%2C%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20INTACH%20notified%20Amar%20Singh%20College%20as%20a%20Grade%201%20heritage%20structure%20in%202004.%20The%20college%20also%20figures%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20Higher%20Education%E2%80%99s%20list%20of%20heritage%20colleges%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%C2%A0However%2C%20the%20state%20government%20has%20not%20notified%20the%20college%20as%20a%20heritage%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20INTACH%20carried%20out%20conservation%20works%20at%20the%20college%20which%20was%20funded%20by%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20government.%20In%202020%2C%20the%20college-related%20work%20was%20one%20of%20seven%20projects%20that%20won%20the%20prestigious%20Award%20of%20Merit%20in%20the%20UNESCO%20Asia-Pacific%20Awards%20for%20Cultural%20Heritage%20Conservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22185823%2Fimage-1997.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22880%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22185823%2Fimage-1997.png%20737w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22185823%2Fimage-1997-300x300.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22185823%2Fimage-1997-150x150.png%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-702881%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22880%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPoplar%20trees%20at%20the%20entrance%20to%20Amar%20Singh%20College%20in%20Srinagar.%20Photo%3A%20X%40Gaamuk%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStudents%20unhappy%20with%20the%20move%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20students%20who%20have%20returned%20to%20the%20college%20after%20the%20culmination%20of%20winter%20vacation%20earlier%20this%20month%20were%20shocked%20and%20visibly%20upset%20by%20the%20scenes%20of%20lopped%20logs%20of%20poplar%20trees%20scattered%20along%20the%20avenue%20which%20they%20had%20once%20beautified%20with%20their%20towering%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20has%20been%20done%20is%20not%20right.%20The%20trees%20didn%E2%80%99t%20kill%20anyone.%20I%20used%20to%20see%20them%20on%20reels%20and%20photos%20of%20the%20college%20before%20I%20joined%20here%20last%20year.%20Now%20they%20are%20nowhere.%20It%20seems%20as%20if%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20college%20has%20been%20erased%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20first-year-student%2C%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20be%20named.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Junaid%20Ahmad%2C%20an%20alumni%2C%20fondly%20recalled%20that%20the%20avenue%20presented%20the%20looks%20of%20a%20green%20tunnel%20which%20showed%20an%20impressive%20view%20of%20the%20main%20heritage%20building.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20avenue%20was%20an%20imposing%20feature%20of%20the%20college%20which%20conveyed%20to%20the%20students%20that%20they%20are%20in%20a%20very%20great%20and%20grand%20space.%20Sadly%20it%20has%20been%20flattened.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArchitects%20and%20environmentalists%20express%20concern%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArchitect%20Saima%20Iqbal%2C%20who%20led%20the%20INTACH%20conservation%20effort%2C%20said%20that%20the%20poplar%20avenues%20were%20important%20landscape%20elements%20for%20enhancing%20entrance%20experience%20of%20buildings%20and%20for%20providing%20vistas%2C%20shade%20and%20formality%20to%20the%20urban%20roads%20in%20the%20early%2020th%20century%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20historic%20avenue.%20It%20has%20a%20permanence%20and%20relevance%20of%20its%20own%2C%20an%20importance%20of%20its%20own%20and%20also%20a%20significance%20of%20its%20own.%20It%20had%20a%20specific%20purpose%20to%20give%20visitors%20a%20guided%20vista%20of%20the%20college.%20What%20has%20been%20done%20is%20a%20catastrophe%2C%E2%80%9D%20Iqbal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Srinagar-based%20environmentalist%2C%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20be%20named%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20college%20has%20%E2%80%9Ceffectively%20wiped%20off%20a%20mini%20carbon%20sink%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20campus.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20avenues%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20the%20preservation%20of%20micro-climatic%20conditions%20and%20also%20filter%20the%20air.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlaming%20the%20college%20management%20for%20the%20move%2C%20Beg%20asserted%20that%20the%20rules%20governing%20the%20conservation%20of%20notified%20heritage%20sites%20should%20have%20been%20factored%20in%20by%20them%20before%20culling%20the%20trees%20which%20are%20%E2%80%9Cequally%20important%E2%80%9D%20from%20a%20heritage%20point%20of%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20official%20guidelines%2C%20any%20proposal%20of%20drastic%20changes%20in%20notified%20heritage%20buildings%20or%20heritage%20landscapes%20has%20to%20be%20approved%20by%20the%20Heritage%20Conservation%20Committee%20which%20is%20headed%20by%20a%20secretary-level%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20guidelines%20mention%20that%20Grade-1%20heritage%20buildings%20%E2%80%9Cdeserve%20careful%20preservation%E2%80%9D%20with%20%E2%80%9Cno%20intervention%E2%80%9D%20allowed%20inside%20the%20heritage%20building%20or%20in%20its%20natural%20features.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20though%20the%20college%20is%20not%20a%20notified%20structure%20but%20by%20extension%20the%20model%20bye%20laws%20should%20ipso%20facto%20apply%20to%20listed%20buildings%20and%20the%20state%20government-declared%20heritage%20colleges.%20Although%20the%20government%20declaration%20was%20meant%20for%20seeking%20funding%20for%20their%20preservation%2C%20but%20that%20definition%20is%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20Beg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArt%20historian%20Hakim%20Sameer%20Hamdani%2C%20who%20has%20led%20major%20heritage%20conservation%20and%20restoration%20efforts%20in%20Srinagar%20underlined%20that%20people%20in%20Kashmir%20are%20not%20generally%20against%20the%20idea%20of%20heritage%2C%20but%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20a%20question%20of%20how%20do%20you%20value%20and%20what%20do%20you%20value%E2%80%9D%20as%20heritage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20understanding%20of%20natural%20heritage%20is%20largely%20limited%20to%20the%20protection%20of%20Chinar%20trees%20and%20Dal%20Lake.%C2%A0%20As%20a%20society%2C%20we%20have%20to%20re-understand%20what%20development%20means%2C%20what%20beautification%20means%20and%20what%20respect%20for%20%5Bthe%5D%20past%20means%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Hamdani%2C%20a%20Srinagar%20resident%20and%20author%20of%20the%20upcoming%20book%20on%20Srinagar%2C%20%E2%80%98City%20of%20Kashmir%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Popular%20History%E2%80%99%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20college%20principal%2C%20a%20batch%20of%20conifers%20planted%20by%20the%20Social%20Forestry%20Department%20along%20the%20avenue%20some%20two%20years%20back%20will%20replace%20the%20poplar%20trees.%20Hamdani%2C%20however%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20non-deciduous%20trees%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20a%20substitute%20for%20poplars%20because%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20allow%20sunlight%20to%20filter%20in%20during%20winter%20months%20which%20can%20aggravate%20cold%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711105250000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22160203%2FScreenshot-2024-03-22-at-3.59.55.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fstudents-historians-miffed-as-administration-cuts-poplar-trees-in-kashmirs-second-oldest-college%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Officials%20said%20234%20poplar%20and%20willow%20trees%20were%20cut.%20The%20plantation%2C%20which%20was%20an%20attraction%20among%20filmmakers%20and%20tourists%20in%20the%20city%2C%20has%20been%20a%20part%20of%20the%20original%20layout%20that%20synchronised%20the%20entries%2C%20pathways%20and%20the%20UNESCO-awarded%20colonial-era%20building%20of%20the%20Amar%20Singh%20College%20which%20was%20built%20in%201913%2C%20art%20conservator%20and%20historian%20Saleem%20Beg%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fstudents-historians-miffed-as-administration-cuts-poplar-trees-in-kashmirs-second-oldest-college%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Whatever%20'Rogue'%20Yarn%20the%20Modi%20Government%20May%20Spin%20on%20Pannun%20Plot%2C%20There%E2%80%99ll%20Be%20No%20Happy%20Ending%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22154553%2FUntitled-design-4-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ECan%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%99s%20security%20be%20entrusted%20to%20a%20government%20which%20allows%20rogue%20operatives%20within%20its%20intelligence%20agencies%20to%20plan%20and%20execute%20clandestine%20assassinations%20in%20friendly%20countries%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20question%20voters%20are%20bound%20to%20ask%20with%20a%20general%20election%20barely%20weeks%20away%2C%20especially%20since%20a%20key%20plank%20on%20which%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20seeking%20a%20third%20term%20as%20prime%20minister%20is%20that%20he%20runs%20a%20stable%20government%20that%20is%20committed%20to%20ensuring%20%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%99s%20security%20and%20has%20succeeded%20in%20enhancing%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20international%20standing%20like%20no%20predecessor%20has%20done%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20these%20claims%20stood%20compromised%20when%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%99s%20principal%20strategic%20partner%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnijjar-pannun-modi-foreign-policy-national-inter